backward compatibility
Avro/Protobuf

Better:

Schema evolution would be managed through Schema Registry using Avro or Protobuf schemas with backward compatibility enforcement.

SDK producers and downstream consumers would follow data contracts, and schema versions would be tracked centrally rather than embedded manually in every payload.

The Bronze layer in S3 would remain append-only and immutable, while schema normalization and compatibility handling would happen in downstream Silver transformations.

10. Multi-Region Design

This answer needs biggest improvement.

You mixed:

